aWFRuleDesc.RuleDescription:
new limit = occurrence limit + (occurrence limit * inflation guard % * (date of loss - effective date of the policy) / 365)
If the inflation guard % is 0, then the limit stays unchanged
aWFRuleDesc.RuleText:
; aWF_RT_Formule (aWPnC_ItemRuleEngine) (Def Version:3) (Implem Version:1)
uses WFTypes
procedure WFCalculate(inOut Result : tWFNum8) var LimitChosen : tWFAmount var InflationGuard : tWFPercent
LimitChosen = self.Option__ItemLimitValue('Building First Year Limit') InflationGuard = self.Option__ItemLimitValue('Inflation Guard %') if InflationGuard = 0 Result = LimitChosen else Result = LimitChosen + LimitChosen * InflationGuard * (self.CurrentDate - self.Option__SubscriptionDate) / 365 endIf endProc

Interest charges on any loan to offset impaired collections pending repayment of such sums made uncollectable by such loss or damage.\par \par 3. Other expense, when reasonably incurred by you in re-establishing records of accounts receivable following loss or damage.\par \par This coverage insures against monetary losses due to damages to (or loss of) the accounts receivable records of the insured because of the following events:\par 1. Breakage of Glass \par 10. Falling Objects \par 11. Weight of Snow, Ice, or Sleet \par 12. Water Damage \par 13. Collapse \par 14. Sprinkler Leakage \par 15. Theft \par 16. All Other Perils\par }
